# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — Difference-in-Differences with Compositional Changes
# Replication package: track code/scripts only. Regenerated outputs and the
# raw application data are excluded (see README). The empty output-directory
# skeleton is preserved via .gitkeep so scripts can write after a fresh clone.
# =============================================================================

# --- OS / editor cruft -------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.Rhistory
.Rapp.history
.RData
.Ruserdata
.Rproj.user/
*.Rproj
# editor swap / backup files (Vim, Emacs, etc.)
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
*~
\#*\#
.\#*

# --- R / Rcpp compiled artifacts ---------------------------------------------
*.o
*.so
*.dll

# --- Scratch / working directories -------------------------------------------
**/temp/
**/tmp/

# --- Generated outputs (produced by the main_* / sim_* / summary scripts) ----
**/results/**
**/tables/**
**/figures/**

# --- Application data: Sequeira (2016, AER) ----------------------------------
# (c) 2016 American Economic Association; data under CC BY 4.0, code under
# BSD-3-Clause. Source: openICPSR https://doi.org/10.3886/E113044V1.
# Redistributed here, unmodified, under CC BY 4.0 (see application/data/LICENSE-*).
# Ignore everything under application/data/ EXCEPT the bundled data + its license.
application/data/**
!application/data/Bribes_Regression.dta
!application/data/LICENSE-Sequeira-2016-AEA.txt

# --- Keep the empty directory skeleton (overrides the rules above) -----------
!**/.gitkeep
